    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1910-05-07T23:59:59-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1910-05-07T00:00:00-05:00" n="603"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d603">
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">British Ambassador</gloss> to the
                            <gloss type="to">Secretary of State</gloss>.</hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">British Embassy</hi>,<lb/>
                            <hi rend="italic">Washington</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1910-05-07">
                            <hi rend="italic">May 7, 1910</hi>
                        </date>.</dateline>
                    <seg rendition="#left">No. 74.]</seg>
                </opener>
                <p>
                    <hi rend="smallcaps">Sir</hi>: I am profoundly grieved to inform you that I have
                    received a cable message from Sir Edward Grey announcing the demise of the King
                    last evening at 11.45.</p>
                <p>It is my melancholy duty to request that you will bring the sad intelligence to
                    the knowledge of the President and his Cabinet.</p>
                <p>I have, etc.,</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">James Bryce.</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
